Just keep doing that.

982
00:54:49,921 --> 00:54:52,883
Oh, don't lose it.

983
00:54:52,924 --> 00:54:55,093
Oh, Lou, you're great.

984
00:54:55,135 --> 00:54:58,055
The leg is better.
You got the cramp out.

985
00:54:58,096 --> 00:55:01,433
You're a wreck.
You gotta start working out.

986
00:55:01,516 --> 00:55:03,268
And you know what else?

987
00:55:03,310 --> 00:55:06,188
You have got midterms
coming up.

988
00:55:06,229 --> 00:55:08,857
You haven't studied five minutes
since you got here.

989
00:55:08,899 --> 00:55:10,067
You're always so neat.

990
00:55:10,108 --> 00:55:11,985
You're just like
your Uncle Vito.

991
00:55:12,027 --> 00:55:14,613
We were kids,
his room was always in order.

992
00:55:14,655 --> 00:55:15,864
His towels lined up neatly...

993
00:55:15,906 --> 00:55:18,075
combs, brushes, hair lotions
all in the right place.

994
00:55:18,116 --> 00:55:20,077
What did it mean?
What is he today?

995
00:55:20,118 --> 00:55:21,620
He's an attendant
in the men's room.

996
00:55:21,662 --> 00:55:24,122
Hey, he's my idol.

997
00:55:24,164 --> 00:55:29,378
But I'm not gonna be
folding towels anymore...

998
00:55:29,419 --> 00:55:32,547
'cause I just made...
ta da... the diving team.

999
00:55:32,589 --> 00:55:35,217
That's great!

1000
00:55:35,258 --> 00:55:36,426
I'm takin' you out.

1001
00:55:36,468 --> 00:55:38,095
We'll celebrate.
We're havin' a party!

1002
00:55:38,136 --> 00:55:40,806
Oh, no, Dad, that's really nice,
but I'm in training now.

1003
00:55:40,847 --> 00:55:43,308
We got a big meet coming up
against Northern.

1004
00:55:43,350 --> 00:55:45,394
We'll have a party
after the meet.

1005
00:55:45,435 --> 00:55:49,398
Dad, why don't you join me
on a little reality break, OK?

1006
00:55:49,439 --> 00:55:51,775
Just 'cause you're in love
with Dr. Turner...

1007
00:55:51,817 --> 00:55:54,611
does not mean you're
gonna pass her course.

1008
00:55:54,653 --> 00:55:57,197
You got a major paper
coming up on Kurt Vonnegut.

1009
00:55:57,239 --> 00:55:59,032
You haven't even read
any of the books.

1010
00:55:59,074 --> 00:56:00,784
I tried.

1011
00:56:00,826 --> 00:56:03,996
I don't understand
a word of it.

1012
00:56:04,997 --> 00:56:08,000
So, how you gonna
write the paper, then?

1013
00:56:12,004 --> 00:56:15,215
Hi, I'm Kurt Vonnegut.
I'm looking for Thornton Melon.

1014
00:56:17,926 --> 00:56:20,554
Want to come in? Dad?

1015
00:56:23,598 --> 00:56:26,393
I don't want to hear
one more word out of you...

1016
00:56:26,435 --> 00:56:28,395
or it's back to the tree.

1017
00:56:28,437 --> 00:56:30,772
Come in.

1018
00:56:30,814 --> 00:56:33,817
Excuse me. Dr. Barazini?

1019
00:56:33,859 --> 00:56:35,235
I'm Thornton Melon.

1020
00:56:35,277 --> 00:56:38,780
Oh, yes, Thornton Melon.
I know you.

1021
00:56:38,822 --> 00:56:42,451
You delivered the paper
on isomagnetic brain waves...

1022
00:56:42,492 --> 00:56:44,036
in Montreal last year.

1023
00:56:44,077 --> 00:56:46,663
No, I sold you your pants.

1024
00:56:46,705 --> 00:56:48,749
Oh, of course.
Good to see you.

1025
00:56:48,790 --> 00:56:50,292
What are you doing here?

1026
00:56:50,334 --> 00:56:52,753
I'm supposed to report here
for my lab project.

1027
00:56:52,794 --> 00:56:55,631
Oh, good. I'm trying to teach
these here apes...

1028
00:56:55,672 --> 00:56:57,424
how to read and write.

1029
00:56:57,466 --> 00:57:00,260
You ought to teach them
how to go to the bathroom.

1030
00:57:00,302 --> 00:57:02,352
You'll get used to that.

1031
00:57:02,387 --> 00:57:07,184
Now, all you have to do
is put a new tape...

1032
00:57:07,225 --> 00:57:10,812
in the tape machine every hour
and observe the animals.

1033
00:57:10,896 --> 00:57:13,065
I'll be back in a few hours
to check on you.

1034
00:57:13,106 --> 00:57:15,651
- OK, fine.
- All righty.

1035
00:57:17,486 --> 00:57:20,822
You don't need this.
I'll find you an organ grinder.

1036
00:57:30,791 --> 00:57:32,918
Hiya, Marge?
A few things.

1037
00:57:32,960 --> 00:57:35,671
I need you and the gang to get
down here as fast as you can.

1038
00:57:35,712 --> 00:57:37,339
And I have to talk to Peterson,
the accountant.

1039
00:57:37,381 --> 00:57:38,757
I'm gonna need him, too.

1040
00:57:38,799 --> 00:57:42,052
Oh, thanks.
And, Marge, I need...

1041
00:57:44,972 --> 00:57:47,224
See if you can get somebody
at the Rand Corporation...

1042
00:57:47,265 --> 00:57:50,185
or the Brookings Institute to
come down here for about a week.

1043
00:57:52,771 --> 00:57:53,981
What?

1044
00:57:55,816 --> 00:57:58,819
And Russell hits him
with a powerful front body slam!

1045
00:58:03,865 --> 00:58:05,117
No problem.

1046
00:58:05,158 --> 00:58:07,536
They're takin' a break,
that's all.

1047
00:58:09,079 --> 00:58:12,687
In 1971, the United States
accumulated deficits...

1048
00:58:12,722 --> 00:58:16,295
greater than the supply
of gold the country held.

1049
00:58:16,336 --> 00:58:18,964
In that year, Richard Nixon...

1050
00:58:19,006 --> 00:58:21,967
took the United States
off the gold standard.

1051
00:58:22,009 --> 00:58:24,386
In doing so, he disrupted...

1052
00:58:26,972 --> 00:58:29,975
the entire international
monetary system.

1053
00:58:30,010 --> 00:58:32,728
What is that clicking noise?

1054
00:58:37,858 --> 00:58:39,901
Are you a student
in this class?

1055
00:58:41,737 --> 00:58:43,155
No.

1056
00:58:43,196 --> 00:58:45,699
Who are you?

1057
00:58:45,741 --> 00:58:48,994
I'm Marge Sweetwater...

1058
00:58:49,036 --> 00:58:51,371
Mr. Thornton Melon's
private secretary.

1059
00:58:58,378 --> 00:59:01,381
What are you doing here?

1060
00:59:01,423 --> 00:59:04,843
I'm taking notes for Mr. Melon.

1061
00:59:08,597 --> 00:59:12,768
He told you to write down
everything I say?

1062
00:59:12,809 --> 00:59:15,562
Yes, he did.

1063
00:59:15,604 --> 00:59:17,022
Good.

1064
00:59:19,483 --> 00:59:21,777
Take this down.

1065
00:59:24,529 --> 00:59:27,908
Mr. Melon,
no matter what you do...

1066
00:59:29,451 --> 00:59:32,329
no matter what stunts
you pull...

1067
00:59:32,412 --> 00:59:35,540
no matter how hard you try...

1068
00:59:35,582 --> 00:59:40,003
you will never, ever
pass this course.

1069
00:59:42,965 --> 00:59:45,425
Make sure he gets that.

1070
00:59:48,470 --> 00:59:50,430
Yes, sir.

1071
00:59:50,472 --> 00:59:51,640
I'll tell you what.

1072
00:59:51,723 --> 00:59:53,892
It's for Barbay.
Make it an "A."

1073
00:59:53,934 --> 00:59:56,103
Where's the lab report
on psychology?

1074
00:59:56,144 --> 00:59:57,479
Here.

1075
00:59:59,481 --> 01:00:02,651
It's too light.
It feels like a "C."

1076
01:00:02,693 --> 01:00:05,904
Bulk it up and add a few
multicolored graphs.

1077
01:00:05,988 --> 01:00:08,615
- Yo, Dad.
- Jason, hold it, will ya?

1078
01:00:08,657 --> 01:00:11,368
Listen, everybody.
Let's see "As" across the board.

1079
01:00:11,410 --> 01:00:12,577
I'll tell you what...

1080
01:00:12,619 --> 01:00:14,997
a ten percent bonus
for every grade over "B."

1081
01:00:15,038 --> 01:00:19,584
And an A+ gets you a free trip
to Hawaii... off-season.

1082
01:00:21,128 --> 01:00:24,965
- Dad, what's going on here?
- I'm doing my homework.

1083
01:00:25,007 --> 01:00:27,217
No, they're doing
your homework.

1084
01:00:27,259 --> 01:00:30,178
A good executive knows how
to delegate authority.

1085
01:00:30,220 --> 01:00:32,848
I took care of you, too.

1086
01:00:32,889 --> 01:00:36,601
- And what's this?
- Your astronomy report.

1087
01:00:36,643 --> 01:00:39,146
- What's wrong with you?
- What's wrong with you?

1088
01:00:39,187 --> 01:00:41,523
I want to write that paper.
I'm gonna write that paper.

1089
01:00:41,565 --> 01:00:44,109
That's why I'm taking astronomy,
to learn something!

1090
01:00:44,151 --> 01:00:46,111
You're never gonna learn
a goddamn thing...

1091
01:00:46,153 --> 01:00:48,155
if you got people
doing your work for you!

1092
01:00:48,196 --> 01:00:50,115
Oh, never mind.

1093
01:00:51,491 --> 01:00:56,121
Kids... they always do things
the hard way.

1094
01:00:56,163 --> 01:01:00,083
Ladies and gentlemen,
the visiting team...

1095
01:01:00,125 --> 01:01:03,378
the Northern University
Wildcats!

1096
01:01:04,838 --> 01:01:09,384
And your Grand Lakes
University Hooters!

1097
01:01:09,426 --> 01:01:12,220
- Hey, there's your boy!
- Jason!

1098
01:01:16,266 --> 01:01:19,394
While the teams are warming up,
we'd like to remind you...

1099
01:01:19,429 --> 01:01:21,480
that all proceeds
from the refreshment stands...

1100
01:01:21,521 --> 01:01:23,148
go to your student government.

1101
01:01:23,190 --> 01:01:25,734
Hey, Valerie. How you doin'?

1102
01:01:25,769 --> 01:01:28,278
Glad you could come. Listen.

1103
01:01:28,320 --> 01:01:31,323
My dad is having a party
tonight at the dorm...

1104
01:01:31,365 --> 01:01:34,242
and it should be pretty great.
His parties usually are.

1105
01:01:34,284 --> 01:01:38,997
I'd love to come,
except for I have a date.

1106
01:01:39,039 --> 01:01:42,501
Oh. Well, hey, bring him along.

1107
01:01:42,542 --> 01:01:45,003
It's OK.
You just both come by.

1108
01:01:45,045 --> 01:01:46,964
I'll really try.

1109
01:01:47,005 --> 01:01:48,966
Good. I hope
I'll see you there.

1110
01:01:49,007 --> 01:01:52,094
It sounds like fun. I wish
my dad were more like yours.

1111
01:02:02,729 --> 01:02:05,357
Hey, Chas.

1112
01:02:05,399 --> 01:02:07,192
Good luck, buddy.
Let's get them.

1113
01:02:07,234 --> 01:02:10,821
Yeah. Thanks, Melon.
I'd wish you luck, too...

1114
01:02:10,862 --> 01:02:12,864
but I guess a guy like you
doesn't need luck.

1115
01:02:13,907 --> 01:02:15,867
What's that supposed to mean?

1116
01:02:15,909 --> 01:02:17,995
With your old man behind you...

1117
01:02:18,036 --> 01:02:20,539
I figured since he bought
your way onto the team...

1118
01:02:20,580 --> 01:02:23,083
he probably bought off
the judges, too.

1119
01:02:27,129 --> 01:02:29,798
Oh, there's Thornton.

1120
01:02:29,840 --> 01:02:31,925
Diane!

1121
01:02:33,510 --> 01:02:37,014
I can't imagine what you can
possibly see in that man.

1122
01:02:37,055 --> 01:02:40,267
Philip, would you excuse me
for a minute?

1123
01:02:44,146 --> 01:02:46,189
Yes, yes.

1124
01:02:46,231 --> 01:02:48,233
- You look great.
- Oh, thanks.

1125
01:02:48,275 --> 01:02:50,068
Where you been?
I called you a hundred times.

1126
01:02:50,110 --> 01:02:52,070
I made four dates
with your answering machine.

1127
01:02:52,112 --> 01:02:54,072
I'm sorry I missed you.
Things have been so hectic.

1128
01:02:54,114 --> 01:02:56,908
I've been reading midterm papers
and grading exams.

1129
01:02:56,950 --> 01:02:58,243
Did you read mine yet?

1130
01:02:58,285 --> 01:03:00,078
Not yet,
but I'm looking forward to it.

1131
01:03:00,162 --> 01:03:02,039
I'm throwing a party
in our room tonight...

1132
01:03:02,080 --> 01:03:03,582
and you better be there.

1133
01:03:03,624 --> 01:03:06,585
I'm sorry. I have a date
with Philip tonight.

1134
01:03:06,627 --> 01:03:10,339
Bring him along.
We may run out of ice.

1135
01:03:13,008 --> 01:03:17,095
First diver
for Grand Lakes University...

1136
01:03:17,137 --> 01:03:19,431
Chas Osbourne.

1137
01:03:42,579 --> 01:03:46,208
Hey, Coach! How are ya?
How you doin', huh?

1138
01:03:50,837 --> 01:03:56,134
Next diver for Grand Lakes...
Jason Melon.

1139
01:03:56,176 --> 01:03:58,470
Melon.

1140
01:04:43,682 --> 01:04:44,766
What's going on?

1141
01:04:44,808 --> 01:04:47,018
This is always
the best party of the year.

1142
01:04:47,053 --> 01:04:49,229
I don't know.
Some big event at the dorms.

1143
01:04:49,271 --> 01:04:52,816
- We're thinkin' of going over.
- To Melon's? Are you nuts?

1144
01:04:52,858 --> 01:04:54,359
Why don't we go?

1145
01:04:54,401 --> 01:04:56,236
Valerie, please.
It'll be horrible.

1146
01:04:56,278 --> 01:04:58,870
Jason said it would be great.
It might be fun.

1147
01:04:58,905 --> 01:05:02,200
Jason's a twerp. We could have
won if it weren't for him.

1148
01:05:02,242 --> 01:05:04,953
Haven't you ever messed up?

1149
01:05:04,995 --> 01:05:06,204
No.

1150
01:05:11,209 --> 01:05:15,839
I'm all dressed up
with nowhere to go

1151
01:05:15,881 --> 01:05:17,633
Hey, baby!

1152
01:05:17,674 --> 01:05:20,886
Walking with a dead man
over my shoulder

1153
01:05:23,639 --> 01:05:26,433
I'm all dressed up
with nowhere to go

1154
01:05:28,810 --> 01:05:31,104
I love three girls at once.

1155
01:05:31,146 --> 01:05:34,191
If I fall asleep,
they have each other to talk to.

1156
01:05:41,782 --> 01:05:44,117
Nice look.
What are you going for?

1157
01:05:44,159 --> 01:05:46,536
The heavy, disassociated
artist thing...

1158
01:05:46,578 --> 01:05:50,332
or the "I'm going blind" thing?

1159
01:05:50,374 --> 01:05:54,294
Oh, It's the deaf thing.
Maybe this will cheer you up.

1160
01:05:54,336 --> 01:05:56,755
Oh, do me!

1161
01:05:56,797 --> 01:05:58,423
Derek! Get up, will ya?

1162
01:05:58,465 --> 01:06:01,635
You look like the poster boy
for birth control.

1163
01:06:05,347 --> 01:06:07,808
Jason, it's a party.
What's your story?

1164
01:06:07,849 --> 01:06:10,852
What's the matter?
The swim meet?

1165
01:06:10,887 --> 01:06:13,855
Forget about it. It's history.

1166
01:06:13,897 --> 01:06:16,233
Come on, will ya? Snap into it!

1167
01:06:16,275 --> 01:06:18,610
You're right, Dad.
It doesn't matter, Dad!

1168
01:06:18,694 --> 01:06:20,779
Right, Dad?
Come on, party, right?

1169
01:06:28,203 --> 01:06:30,414
Hey, buddy!

1170
01:06:30,455 --> 01:06:32,749
Everybody, make some noise,
have some fun!

1171
01:06:39,172 --> 01:06:40,966
What's that noise?

1172
01:06:41,008 --> 01:06:43,051
It's a party, Philip.
Midterms, remember?

1173
01:06:43,135 --> 01:06:45,595
They're just blowing off steam.

1174
01:06:45,637 --> 01:06:46,847
You there.

1175
01:06:49,266 --> 01:06:50,517
What's going on here?

1176
01:06:50,559 --> 01:06:54,771
The Melon man is throwing
the greatest party of all time!

1177
01:06:54,813 --> 01:06:57,899
The whole world is there.
It's the best thing...

1178
01:06:57,941 --> 01:07:00,235
that's ever happened to me
in my whole life!

1179
01:07:00,277 --> 01:07:02,613
Oh, God.

1180
01:07:06,992 --> 01:07:08,994
Look at that!

1181
01:07:09,036 --> 01:07:10,203
Listen to that racket.

1182
01:07:10,245 --> 01:07:12,497
This is disgraceful.
I should phone security.

1183
01:07:12,539 --> 01:07:14,207
Oh, Philip.

1184
01:07:19,129 --> 01:07:22,341
Good. Apparently I'm not
the only one around here...

1185
01:07:22,382 --> 01:07:23,925
with a sense of decency.

1186
01:07:30,223 --> 01:07:32,059
Yeah. Cool!

1187
01:07:35,854 --> 01:07:38,315
Did you see...
where are you going?

1188
01:07:38,357 --> 01:07:40,317
Intellectual curiosity, Philip.

1189
01:07:40,359 --> 01:07:41,693
Sounds fun in there.
Come with me.

1190
01:07:41,735 --> 01:07:44,655
- Oh, please!
- Oh, Philip!

1191
01:07:48,533 --> 01:07:51,036
It's a dead man's party

1192
01:07:51,078 --> 01:07:53,205
Who could ask for more

1193
01:07:54,289 --> 01:07:56,208
Everybody's coming

1194
01:07:56,249 --> 01:07:59,211
Leave your body
at the door

1195
01:07:59,252 --> 01:08:03,048
Leave your body and soul
at the door

1196
01:08:04,049 --> 01:08:06,551
Don't run away

1197
01:08:06,635 --> 01:08:09,388
It's only me

1198
01:08:16,269 --> 01:08:18,438
Don't run away

1199
01:08:18,480 --> 01:08:21,775
It's only me, only me

1200
01:08:21,817 --> 01:08:25,112
Don't be afraid

1201
01:08:25,153 --> 01:08:29,574
Of what you can't see

1202
01:08:29,616 --> 01:08:31,785
Say when.

1203
01:08:31,827 --> 01:08:34,454
Right after this drink.

1204
01:08:34,496 --> 01:08:37,019
Hey, what's a bath
without Bubbles?

1205
01:08:37,054 --> 01:08:39,543
Hey, Bubbles,
come over here, will ya?

1206
01:08:41,837 --> 01:08:44,423
Well!

1207
01:08:44,464 --> 01:08:46,717
- Hi there.
- Hi!

1208
01:08:46,758 --> 01:08:48,927
- What's your favorite subject?
- Poetry.

1209
01:08:48,969 --> 01:08:52,931
Really? Maybe you can help me
straighten out my Longfellow.

1210
01:08:56,685 --> 01:08:58,770
Excuse me.
Have you seen Thornton Melon?

1211
01:08:58,812 --> 01:09:00,606
I think he's in there.

1212
01:09:00,647 --> 01:09:01,815
Thanks.

1213
01:09:08,238 --> 01:09:11,158
Excuse me.
Has anyone seen Thornton Melon?

1214
01:09:12,326 --> 01:09:14,911
That's what I call
marine biology.

1215
01:09:14,953 --> 01:09:16,371
Diane!

1216
01:09:18,040 --> 01:09:20,167
Say hello to my nieces.

1217
01:09:21,710 --> 01:09:23,170
Wait a minute!

1218
01:09:27,841 --> 01:09:32,262
Jason? There you are.
I was looking all over for you.

1219
01:09:32,304 --> 01:09:36,350
Jason, are you OK?
I'm sorry about the swim meet.

1220
01:09:36,391 --> 01:09:39,603
Shit. Swim meet.

1221
01:09:39,645 --> 01:09:42,397
Jesus, you think I care
about the swim meet?

1222
01:09:42,439 --> 01:09:44,274
I mean, it's just
a stupid college game.

1223
01:09:44,316 --> 01:09:45,657
It's just bullshit.

1224
01:09:45,692 --> 01:09:47,653
Why are you acting like this?

1225
01:09:47,694 --> 01:09:49,696
I know you don't think
like that.

1226
01:09:49,738 --> 01:09:52,032
Oh, you do?

